<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer7570100316369266778">Wendell Berry is a conservationist, farmer, essayist, novelist, professor of English and poet. He was born August 5, 1934 in Henry County, Kentucky where he now lives on a farm. The New York Times has called Berry the &quot;prophet of rural America.&quot;</span>
  <span id="freeText7570100316369266778" style="display:none">Wendell Berry is a conservationist, farmer, essayist, novelist, professor of English and poet. He was born August 5, 1934 in Henry County, Kentucky where he now lives on a farm. The New York Times has called Berry the "prophet of rural America."</span>
  <a data-text-id="7570100316369266778" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

</div>
